by headings if they like.


486
00:23:59,026 --> 00:24:00,836
That Info button it accessible.


487
00:24:01,076 --> 00:24:05,286
We still need a way to add
something to the favorite list,


488
00:24:06,066 --> 00:24:09,366
and the favorite graph
is still inaccessible.


489
00:24:10,316 --> 00:24:14,566
How would we make
this graph accessible?


490
00:24:15,596 --> 00:24:17,916
So let's start by going back


491
00:24:17,916 --> 00:24:19,706
to those questions we were
talking about earlier.


492
00:24:19,916 --> 00:24:21,476
The first one was:
Do I serve a purpose?


493
00:24:21,536 --> 00:24:24,666
So there is a lot of
information being communicated


494
00:24:24,666 --> 00:24:29,016
in this graph, but not all of
it is really serving a purpose


495
00:24:29,016 --> 00:24:30,186
or really important to the user.


496
00:24:30,186 --> 00:24:32,226
So what's the most
important bits in this graph?


497
00:24:32,226 --> 00:24:34,366
I think that's the points,


498
00:24:34,796 --> 00:24:36,876
because they tell us exactly
what we are comparing,


499
00:24:37,046 --> 00:24:39,376
so that's probably what
we should make accessible.


500
00:24:40,666 --> 00:24:43,316
The next question that's worth
talking about is: Where am I?


501
00:24:43,676 --> 00:24:45,866
So what do we set for
the accessibility frame


502
00:24:46,026 --> 00:24:46,656
for these points?


503
00:24:47,866 --> 00:24:50,596
So you might think
that the orange boxes


504
00:24:50,596 --> 00:24:55,696
that you see now are a
good idea, but if you look


505
00:24:55,696 --> 00:24:59,066
at the view as a whole,
most of it isn't accessible.


506
00:24:59,946 --> 00:25:03,806
So most of it is
just dead space,


507
00:25:04,216 --> 00:25:06,846
and so as a VoiceOver
user slides their finger


508
00:25:06,846 --> 00:25:09,526
around the screen to search for
points, it will be mostly empty.


509
00:25:10,236 --> 00:25:13,456
A better frame might
be something like this.


510
00:25:13,946 --> 00:25:16,626
So a VoiceOver user can
slide his or her finger


511
00:25:16,626 --> 00:25:18,416
across the screen,
and they will hit all


512
00:25:18,416 --> 00:25:19,496
of the points as they do so.


513
00:25:19,496 --> 00:25:22,316
And then as long as we set
the accessibility value


514
00:25:22,316 --> 00:25:24,616
to the magnitude, we
haven't lost anything.


515
00:25:24,616 --> 00:25:26,446
We haven't lost any information.


516
00:25:26,766 --> 00:25:28,556
So that seems like a good plan.


517
00:25:29,456 --> 00:25:30,896
Unfortunately, I happen to know


518
00:25:30,896 --> 00:25:33,976
that the graph view
is just one big view,


519
00:25:33,976 --> 00:25:36,296
and everything is drawn
directly into the view.


520
00:25:36,696 --> 00:25:42,056
So how do we make one view
accessible into multiple parts?


521
00:25:42,896 --> 00:25:45,406
And the good news is we have
got an API for that as well,


522
00:25:45,406 --> 00:25:47,176
UIAccessibility element.


523
00:25:47,236 --> 00:25:51,286
So this is a great way to
create specific objects just


524
00:25:51,286 --> 00:25:54,416
for accessibility to break
up a view into subelements


525
00:25:54,816 --> 00:25:57,186
and still answer those great
six questions we have been


526
00:25:57,186 --> 00:25:57,826
talking about.


527
00:25:58,486 --> 00:26:01,266
The only new part is the
accessibility container,


528
00:26:01,266 --> 00:26:03,136
which you would just set
to the containing view.


529
00:26:04,106 --> 00:26:07,616
Great! So with this API, we
can make the graph accessible.


530
00:26:08,216 --> 00:26:10,506
How do we add something
to that favorite list


531
00:26:10,816 --> 00:26:12,686
so there is something
to display on the graph?


532
00:26:13,276 --> 00:26:17,036
For that I think we should use
Accessibility Perform Magic Tap,


533
00:26:17,626 --> 00:26:18,716
which is this really cool API


534
00:26:18,716 --> 00:26:21,626
to just do the right thing
in the right context.


535
00:26:22,416 --> 00:26:24,436
A good example of that is


536
00:26:24,516 --> 00:26:26,096
when a VoiceOver user
gets a phone call,


537
00:26:26,306 --> 00:26:29,666
they can do the Magic Tap
gesture, which is two fingers,


538
00:26:30,006 --> 00:26:32,776
double-tap on the screen, and
that will do the magic thing,


539
00:26:32,866 --> 00:26:34,576
which is answer the phone call.


540
00:26:35,406 --> 00:26:38,496
So that will allow us to add
something to the favorite list,


541
00:26:39,446 --> 00:26:41,376
but what do we add to the list?


542
00:26:42,256 --> 00:26:44,046
And for that we can
use some brand-new API


543
00:26:44,206 --> 00:26:46,846
in iOS 9 called Accessibility
Focus.


544
00:26:46,956 --> 00:26:50,256
This will allow you to get
the currently focused element


545
00:26:50,436 --> 00:26:51,956
for a given assistive technology


546
00:26:52,256 --> 00:26:53,726
like VoiceOver or
Switch Control.


547
00:26:54,436 --> 00:26:56,486
If you are interested in
tracking focus as it moves


548
00:26:56,486 --> 00:26:59,196
around your app, we
provide a notification


549
00:26:59,536 --> 00:27:02,216
that will tell you the
currently focused element


550
00:27:02,406 --> 00:27:03,706
and the previously
focused element


551
00:27:03,706 --> 00:27:05,086
for a given assistive
technology.


552
00:27:05,796 --> 00:27:08,356
We know what to add
to the favorites list,


553
00:27:08,356 --> 00:27:11,186
we know how to add it, and
then we can explore the graph.


554
00:27:11,496 --> 00:27:14,596
So let's look at
implementing that now.


555
00:27:20,116 --> 00:27:20,546
All right.


556
00:27:20,626 --> 00:27:22,036
Back in Xcode.


557
00:27:23,096 --> 00:27:26,986
So let's add something
to the favorite list.


558
00:27:27,986 --> 00:27:29,576
So if we go to the app delegate,


559
00:27:30,746 --> 00:27:35,956
we can add Accessibility
Perform Magic Tap.


560
00:27:36,266 --> 00:27:39,526
So we will grab the currently
focused element for VoiceOver,


561
00:27:40,366 --> 00:27:43,246
check if that element
responds to toggle favorite,


562
00:27:43,276 --> 00:27:46,286
like the cell, and if it
does, we will ask it to toggle


563
00:27:46,286 --> 00:27:47,696
as favorite and then return Yes.


564
00:27:48,206 --> 00:27:49,506
Otherwise, we return No,


565
00:27:49,946 --> 00:27:52,416
and VoiceOver will do the
next-most-magical thing


566
00:27:52,566 --> 00:27:54,356
in that context,
whatever that may be.


567
00:27:54,856 --> 00:27:59,186
So that will allow us to add
something to the favorite list.


568
00:27:59,616 --> 00:28:01,456
Now, let's look at the graph.


569
00:28:02,556 --> 00:28:03,716
All right.


570
00:28:03,766 --> 00:28:07,096
So it looks like I'm
drawing it with CAShapeLayer,


571
00:28:07,236 --> 00:28:09,526
which is a great way to draw
a graph, but not a great way


572
00:28:09,526 --> 00:28:11,586
to draw an accessible graph.


573
00:28:11,836 --> 00:28:15,456
So down here I'm actually
grabbing the point


574
00:28:15,596 --> 00:28:16,966
and drawing it.


575
00:28:17,616 --> 00:28:19,056
So that seems like a good place


576
00:28:19,096 --> 00:28:22,366
to create my UIAccessibility
element.


577
00:28:23,946 --> 00:28:28,376
So I create a UIAccessibility
element, setting its container


578
00:28:28,376 --> 00:28:30,096
to Self, the graph view.


579
00:28:30,146 --> 00:28:35,186
And then I set its label to a
formatted version of the date.


580
00:28:35,816 --> 00:28:37,336
So we know when it happened.


581
00:28:37,846 --> 00:28:40,456
We will set the value to
the magnitude description.


582
00:28:40,966 --> 00:28:42,146
That's good.


583
00:28:42,266 --> 00:28:45,976
And then like we talked about,
I will take the frame and set it


584
00:28:45,976 --> 00:28:49,216
to slightly wider
than the point,


585
00:28:49,746 --> 00:28:51,756
and the full height
of the graph.


586
00:28:51,756 --> 00:28:56,226
I will set that as the
frame after converting it


587
00:28:56,306 --> 00:28:57,676
to screen coordinates.


588
00:28:58,496 --> 00:29:03,576
And finally add that to
an array that I had ready,


589
00:29:03,976 --> 00:29:06,396
and set that as the
accessibility elements


590
00:29:06,756 --> 00:29:07,436
for the graph view.


591
00:29:08,456 --> 00:29:10,396
So just a few more
lines of code.


592
00:29:10,936 --> 00:29:12,976
Let's see what that looks like.


593
00:29:18,516 --> 00:29:19,066
All right.


594
00:29:19,116 --> 00:29:22,066
So I will triple-tap
Home and start VoiceOver.


595
00:29:22,196 --> 00:29:22,816
>> VOICEOVER: VoiceOver on.


596
00:29:23,136 --> 00:29:25,096
FaceTime, QuakeWatch.


597
00:29:25,936 --> 00:29:26,826
Double-tap to open.


598
00:29:26,826 --> 00:29:27,316
QuakeWatch.


599
00:29:27,616 --> 00:29:28,646
Earthquakes, heading.


600
00:29:28,936 --> 00:29:30,086
>> IAN FISCH: There's
those beautiful cells.


601
00:29:30,086 --> 00:29:33,386
I will do the Magic Tap
gesture, which is two fingers,


602
00:29:33,386 --> 00:29:34,566
double-tap on the screen.


603
00:29:35,276 --> 00:29:39,196
And there it is,
now it's a favorite.


604
00:29:39,386 --> 00:29:40,476
>> VOICEOVER: 12 kilometers.


605
00:29:40,726 --> 00:29:43,926
California 2015.


606
00:29:44,096 --> 00:29:46,116
11:10 a.m. Favorite.


607
00:29:46,496 --> 00:29:47,546
>> IAN FISCH: It
says it's a favorite.


608
00:29:47,646 --> 00:29:48,586
That's good.


609
00:29:49,106 --> 00:29:50,026
So let's add a few more.


610
00:29:51,356 --> 00:29:54,196
First, we have to wait
for earthquakes to happen.


611
00:29:54,196 --> 00:29:55,186
All right.


612
00:29:55,856 --> 00:29:57,786
Three should be enough.


613
00:29:58,906 --> 00:30:00,206
>> VOICEOVER: Detail,
back button.


614
00:30:01,466 --> 00:30:02,366
>> IAN FISCH: Let's
see what happens


