00:30:16,276 --> 00:30:19,856
I should hit all of them.


621
00:30:20,066 --> 00:30:23,486
And that's how you make
a graphic accessible,


622
00:30:23,486 --> 00:30:24,976
an earthquake graph
accessible, at least.


623
00:30:25,786 --> 00:30:27,836
So just a few lines of
code, and we were able


624
00:30:27,836 --> 00:30:32,306
to clean all of that up.


625
00:30:32,696 --> 00:30:33,786
Let's take one more look,


626
00:30:33,786 --> 00:30:35,996
we have the earthquake
cell is now accessible,


627
00:30:35,996 --> 00:30:37,596
not using yellow
anymore, thank goodness.


628
00:30:38,186 --> 00:30:40,156
The map detail is accessible.


629
00:30:40,526 --> 00:30:43,186
We can add a favorite
using the Magic Tap,


630
00:30:44,146 --> 00:30:47,256
and we can even explore the
graph and compare earthquakes,


631
00:30:47,746 --> 00:30:49,256
our favorite earthquakes,
at least.


632
00:30:50,586 --> 00:30:52,826
So just a few lines of
code, just a few minutes,


633
00:30:52,826 --> 00:30:55,816
and we were able to take an app
that was completely unusable


634
00:30:55,816 --> 00:30:59,526
for VoiceOver users and make
it probably the most accessible


635
00:30:59,526 --> 00:31:01,496
earthquake tracking
app out there.


636
00:31:04,926 --> 00:31:08,156
Remember that accessibility
is about users.


637
00:31:08,346 --> 00:31:09,896
Thinking about how users


638
00:31:09,896 --> 00:31:11,926
of all abilities will
interact with your app.


639
00:31:12,596 --> 00:31:14,776
Remember everyone that's
going to be using your app


640
00:31:14,776 --> 00:31:16,686
as you are designing it.


